  "prompt": "What is origin of \"Nehru\" surname?",
  "response": "The surname \"Nehru\" has its origins in the Kashmiri Pandit community, which is a Brahmin community native to the Kashmir Valley in India. The name \"Nehru\" is derived from the Persian word \"Nahr,\" which means \"river.\" It is believed that the surname was adopted by the family due to their residence near the Jhelum River (also known as the Nehr-e-Kashmir in Persian).\n\nThe Nehru family became prominent in Indian history, particularly through Motilal Nehru and his son Jawaharlal Nehru, who were key figures in the Indian independence movement and early governance of independent India. Jawaharlal Nehru, affectionately known as Pandit Nehru, became the first Prime Minister of India after the country gained independence from British rule in 1947.\n\nThe surname \"Nehru\" thus reflects the family's Kashmiri Brahmin heritage and their connection to the region of Kashmir.",
